section.section:
Of the 8 registered nurse members:
1 shall be certified in an advanced practice nursing specialty that rotates with each vacancy among the following specialties:
Nurse anesthetist;
Nurse practitioner;
Nurse midwife; and
Nurse psychotherapist;
1 shall be a baccalaureate nursing educator with, at least, a master's degree in nursing or education;
1 shall be an associate degree nursing educator with, at least, a master's degree in nursing or education;
1 shall be a practical nursing educator with, at least, a bachelor of science degree in nursing or education;
1 shall be a nurse administrator with, at least, a master's degree in nursing administration, business administration, business management, education, or public health;
1 shall be a nurse clinician with at least a master's degree in nursing or public health;
1 shall be a currently practicing nurse, who has practiced acute care for at least 5 years, with a bachelor of science degree in nursing; and
1 shall be a currently practicing nurse who has practiced as a delegating nurse in a supervised group living setting, as defined in COMAR 10.27.11.02(20), for at least 5 years.

The Governor shall appoint:
The registered nurse member certified in an advanced practice nursing specialty, with the advice of the Secretary, from a list of qualified individuals jointly developed in accordance with the requirements of subsection (a)(3)(i) of this section and submitted to the Secretary and the Governor by the:
Maryland Association of Nurse Anesthetists, Inc.;
Nurse Practitioners Association of Maryland, Inc.;
Maryland Coalition of Nurse Practitioners, Inc.;
Maryland Chapter, American College of Nurse-Midwives; and
Psychiatric Advance Practice Nurses of Maryland; and
The other registered nurse members, with the advice of the Secretary, from:
A list of qualified individuals submitted to the Secretary and the Governor by:
A valid petition submitted to the Secretary and the Governor by a registered nurse with an active license under this title.

text.section:
Each consumer member of the Board:
Shall be a member of the general public;
May not be or ever have been a registered nurse or licensed practical nurse or in training to become a registered nurse or licensed practical nurse;
May not have a household member who is a registered nurse or licensed practical nurse or in training to become a registered nurse or licensed practical nurse;
May not participate or ever have participated in a commercial or professional field related to registered nursing or licensed practical nursing;
May not have a household member who participates in a commercial or professional field related to registered nursing or licensed practical nursing; or
May not have had within 2 years before appointment a substantial financial interest in a person who is regulated by the Board.
